[30;1m184 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m185 | [0m[35mManagement Information Base (MIB) can be thought of as a formal[0m
[30;1m186 | [0m[35mdescription of a collection of relevant managed objects whose values[0m
[30;1m187 | [0m[35mcollectively reflect the current "state" of some subsystem at a[0m
[30;1m188 | [0m[35mmanaged entity. These values may be queried, modified by or reported[0m
[30;1m189 | [0m[35mto a managing entity by sending SNMP messages to the agent that is[0m
[30;1m190 | [0m[35mexecuting in a managed node.[0m

[30;1m2 | [0m[35mHow to implement MIB at the Agent[0m
[30;1m3 | [0m[35m---------------------------------[0m
[30;1m4 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35mQ. How to instantiate static MIB table at my SNMP Agent?[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35mA. You need to create MibScalarInstance class instances and register [0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35m   them with your Agent's SNMP engine (mibBuilder, more specifically).[0m
